{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4a36ea56-25bb-4158-8768-42b43b4d2865","content":"Run this:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis combines `dotnet watch` (hot reload — re-runs on file save) with `--filter` to match only that test by name. You can edit your `.cs` files and tests will automatically re-run on save, scoped to just that one test.\n\n**Shorthand alternative** using the display name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\n`Name=` requires an exact match; `FullyQualifiedName~` does a contains match (useful if you don't want to type the full namespace).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"49030d9c-71e0-42f4-96a0-eccfba87660a","outputTokens":174,"requestId":"300C:DE6C9:490972C:4FD3D25:6A0310EB"},"id":"3977a4c5-d447-451c-b2cf-19216b674879","timestamp":"2026-05-12T11:37:22.383Z","parentId":"4165d0cf-afbb-4169-b4f0-873b182e933a"}
